OL,3,C'No plan B' for professional rugby in
OL,4,CWales, admits WRU chair
OL,6,FThe chair of the Welsh Rugby Union has
OL,7,Fadmitted there is "no plan B" for the
OL,8,Ffuture of professional rugby in Wales
OL,9,Fshould he lose in a proposed vote of
OL,10,Fno confidence.
OL,12,FRichard Collier-Keywood's leadership
OL,13,Fis under threat after member clubs
OL,14,Fcalled for an Extraordinary General
OL,15,FMeeting (EGM). Under union rules, the
OL,16,Fmeeting must be held by 12 April,
OL,17,Fthough a specific date has yet to be
OL,18,Fconfirmed.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/8
