OL,3,C'No plan B' for professional rugby in
OL,4,CWales, admits WRU chair
OL,6,FIt comes following ongoing controversy
OL,7,Faround attempts by the WRU to reduce
OL,8,Fthe number of clubs in Wales from four
OL,9,Fto three, which could see the end of
OL,10,FSwansea-based side, the Ospreys.
OL,12,FAppearing before the Senedd's Culture
OL,13,Fand Sport Committee on Thursday, 26
OL,14,FFebruary, Collier-Keywood was asked
OL,15,Fdirectly if a contingency plan existed
OL,16,Ffor the professional game if his
OL,17,Fcurrent strategy was rejected.
OL,19,F"In terms of professional rugby, no,
OL,20,Fwe don't have a plan B for that," he
OL,21,Ftold MSs.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1772381499
OL,3,C'No plan B' for professional rugby in
OL,4,CWales, admits WRU chair
OL,6,FHowever, he insisted the governing
OL,7,Fbody would not be caught unprepared
OL,8,Ffor a change at the top: "We will
OL,9,Fprepare for the situation if I am
OL,10,Fvoted out at the EGM; of course we
OL,11,Fwill prepare for that as part of the
OL,12,Fprocess."
OL,14,FMr Collier-Keywood defended his
OL,15,Frecord, pointing to a professionalised
OL,16,Fgovernance structure and a
OL,17,F"significant" cultural shift within an
OL,18,Forganisation previously dogged by
OL,19,Fscandal.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1772381499
OL,3,C'No plan B' for professional rugby in
OL,4,CWales, admits WRU chair
OL,6,FHe further highlighted the union's
OL,7,Fprogress in the women's game and
OL,8,Fclaimed he had finally placed the
OL,9,FWRU's finances on a "stable footing."
OL,11,F"My mandate was change," he told the
OL,12,Fcommittee, "I think we are on course
OL,13,Ffor delivering that change.
OL,15,F"We recognise that is very painful,
OL,16,Fbut we are committed to delivering it.
OL,17,FThat's why you asked me to do this
OL,18,Fjob; you didn't ask me to do this job
OL,19,Fto keep the status quo."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
